Usage: assignPGBumps [-help] [-connectType {ioring corering stripe iopin}]
                     -nets <net+> [-V  | -H  | -checkerboard ] [-selected  | -floating  | -bumps <bump+>] [-checkerboard  [-square <width height>]]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-H                         # specifies the style of bump assignment as
                           # horizontal (bool, required)
-V                         # specifies the style of bump assignment as vertical
                           # (bool, required)
-bumps <bump+>             # specifies the bumps to be assigned
                           # ((bump)+, required)
-checkerboard              # specifies the style of bump assignment as
                           # checkerboard (bool, required)
-connectType {ioring corering stripe iopin}
                           # specifies the bump connect type (enum, optional)
-floating                  # assigns to floating bumps (bool, required)
-nets <net+>               # specifies the net names ((net)+, required)
-selected                  # assigns to selected bumps (bool, required)
-square <width height>     # It specifies the width and height of square of
                           # checkerboard. (point, optional)